    "title": "Power Analysis for Linear Mixed Models: What You Need to Know",
    "section": "Setup",
    "text": "Setup\nWe’ll simulate a dataset mimicking a repeated-measures experiment, fit a mixed model, and then use simr for power estimation.\n\n# Load required libraries\nlibrary(lme4)\n\nLoading required package: Matrix\n\nlibrary(simr)\n\nWarning: package 'simr' was built under R version 4.3.3\n\n\n\nAttaching package: 'simr'\n\n\nThe following object is masked from 'package:lme4':\n\n    getData\n\nlibrary(ggplot2)"
  },
  {
    "objectID": "posts/power-analysis-lmm/index.html#simulate-data",
    "href": "posts/power-analysis-lmm/index.html#simulate-data",
    "title": "Power Analysis for Linear Mixed Models: What You Need to Know",
    "section": "Simulate Data",
    "text": "Simulate Data\n\nset.seed(123)\nn_subjects &lt;- 30\nn_obs &lt;- 5\nsubject &lt;- factor(rep(1:n_subjects, each = n_obs))\ntime &lt;- rep(1:n_obs, n_subjects)\nintercept &lt;- 2\nslope &lt;- 0.5\nsubject_effect &lt;- rnorm(n_subjects, 0, 1)\ny &lt;- intercept + slope * time + rep(subject_effect, each = n_obs) + rnorm(n_subjects * n_obs, 0, 1)\n\ndata &lt;- data.frame(subject, time, y)"
  },
  {
    "objectID": "posts/power-analysis-lmm/index.html#fit-the-linear-mixed-model",
    "href": "posts/power-analysis-lmm/index.html#fit-the-linear-mixed-model",
    "title": "Power Analysis for Linear Mixed Models: What You Need to Know",
    "section": "Fit the Linear Mixed Model",
    "text": "Fit the Linear Mixed Model\n\nmodel &lt;- lmer(y ~ time + (1 | subject), data = data)\nsummary(model)\n\nLinear mixed model fit by REML ['lmerMod']\nFormula: y ~ time + (1 | subject)\n   Data: data\n\nREML criterion at convergence: 475.3\n\nScaled residuals: \n    Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max \n-2.1543 -0.6120 -0.0704  0.5355  3.2277 \n\nRandom effects:\n Groups   Name        Variance Std.Dev.\n subject  (Intercept) 1.0009   1.0004  \n Residual             0.9421   0.9706  \nNumber of obs: 150, groups:  subject, 30\n\nFixed effects:\n            Estimate Std. Error t value\n(Intercept)  2.02252    0.26059   7.761\ntime         0.48206    0.05604   8.602\n\nCorrelation of Fixed Effects:\n     (Intr)\ntime -0.645"
  },
